# Financial Analyst Agent — Linux cron schedule
# Runs Mon/Wed/Fri at 7am local time
#
# Install: crontab -e  (then paste the line below, adjusting the path)
#
# ┌───── minute (0)
# │ ┌─── hour (7)
# │ │ ┌─ day of month (*)
# │ │ │ ┌ month (*)
# │ │ │ │ ┌ day of week (1=Mon, 3=Wed, 5=Fri)
# │ │ │ │ │
0 7 * * 1,3,5 cd /path/to/financial-analyst-agent && /path/to/uv run python run_pipeline.py >> logs/cron.log 2>&1

# ── Notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Replace /path/to/financial-analyst-agent with your actual project directory.
# Replace /path/to/uv with the output of: which uv
# Example (assuming uv installed to ~/.local/bin):
# 0 7 * * 1,3,5 cd /home/user/financial-analyst-agent && /home/user/.local/bin/uv run python run_pipeline.py >> logs/cron.log 2>&1
#
# To run the refresh poller as a background service on Linux, use systemd instead:
# See: https://systemd.io/ — create a .service unit for poll_refresh.py
